Preamble
========
The SKYIOUS Software License is a file-level copyleft license that
balances freedom for users with protection for the original project.
It ensures that modifications to individual files remain under the
same license while allowing the project maintainers to incorporate
improvements from forks back into the main project. Attribution is
required in both documentation and user interfaces.

Definitions
===========
"You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising
permissions granted by this License.

"Licensed Work" means the software, firmware, or documentation covered
by this License, including any modifications or additions.

"Source" form means the preferred form for making modifications,
including but not limited to source code, configuration files, and
build scripts.

"You" includes any entity that receives a copy of the Licensed Work.

"Maintainer" means the original project team, including the original
copyright holder and their designated contributors, who maintain the
official upstream repository of the Licensed Work.

"Fork" means a copy of the Licensed Work that is modified and
distributed separately from the Maintainer's official repository.

